                            <comment id="17683180" author="paulk" created="Thu, 2 Feb 2023 00:12:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you are wanting default values and tuple constructors and map-like constructors, the now recommended approach to achieve what you are after in Groovy 4 is to leave out &lt;tt&gt;@MapConstructor&lt;/tt&gt; and instead use the &lt;tt&gt;namedVariant&lt;/tt&gt; attribute with &lt;tt&gt;@TupleConstructor&lt;/tt&gt;, i.e. use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@TupleConstructor(includeFields = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;, namedVariant = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
